.TH SIMPLE_SHELL 1 "Nov 21, 2020" "1.0" "Simple shell man page"

.SH NAME

 simple_shell \- The simple_shell take input from user and executes said command if found.

.SH SYNOPSIS

.B $ [args][flag]

.SH DESCRIPTION

A Unix shell is a command-line interpreter or shell that provides a command line user interface for Unix-like operating systems. The shell is both an interactive command language and a scripting language, and is used by the operating system to control the execution of the system using shell scripts.

.SH EXAMPLES

.B $ pwd

     /home/vagrant/simple_shell

----------------------------------------------------------------------

.B $ ls

01_simple_shell_0.1   05_simple_shell_0.3  check_simple_shell.bash  dirsearch.c  getenviron.c	man_1_simple_shell  simple_shell 02_simple_shell_0.1.1
README.m  checkfunction.c exe helper1.c	shell.c token.c 03_simple_shell_0.2 addnode.c config execute.c helper2.c shell.h
.SH RETURN

    The shell returns a number from an exit statment that tells where the code failed. It also returns boolean values depending on the function.

.SH OPTIONS

.B env
 - This displays the current environment on your terminal when prompted with env command.

.B pwd
 - This displays the current working on your teminal when prompted with pwd command.

.B PATH
 - This displays the current PATH variable on your terminal when prompted with the PATH command.

.B ls
 - This displys the current files in your working directory.

